---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../site.config';
import { withBase } from '../lib/url';

const title = 'About';
const description = `About ${SITE.name} — who writes it and how each post gets made.`;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>About {SITE.name}</h1>

  <p>
    Hi, I'm {SITE.author}. {SITE.name} is where I break down AI writing, coding, image,
    and productivity tools — what they actually do, how they compare, and where the
    marketing oversells them. I focus on the questions I'd actually want answered before
    spending money or time on a tool, not on rewriting press releases.
  </p>

  <h2>How posts get made</h2>
  <p>
    Drafts start as AI-assisted research and writing, then I personally review and edit
    every post before it goes up — checking claims, cutting anything that doesn't hold
    up, and adding real context where I have it. I'm upfront that not every post reflects
    hands-on testing of every tool covered yet; where a claim is genuinely from my own use,
    it reads that way, and where it's drawn from public information or reporting, I try to
    keep the framing honest about that rather than implying first-hand experience I don't
    have. I'm not paid for positive coverage.
  </p>

  <h2>Advertising</h2>
  <p>
    This site is supported by display advertising (including Google AdSense) and may,
    in the future, include affiliate links clearly marked as such. Advertising and
    affiliate relationships never determine my conclusions.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions, corrections, or tips? Reach out on the <a href={withBase('/contact')}>contact page</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
